label: AB_tP64_92_2a3b_4b-001
title: Intermediate Temperature Tetragonal TlS Structure
comments: TlS occurs naturally in three forms (Villars, 2018): \begin{itemize} \item The ground state is tetragonal in the \href{current_web_home_dir/AB_tI16_140_ab_h-001}{TlSe ($B37$) structure} which (Villars, 2018) calls ``Tet-I'' and (Kishida, 1994) calls ``Type I.'' \item An intermediate \href{current_web_home_dir/AB_tP64_92_2a3b_4b-001}{tetragonal structure}, which (Villars, 2018) calls ``Tetragonal II,'' and (Kashida, 1994) calls Type III. (this structure) \item A high temperature \href{current_web_home_dir/AB_mC256_5_2a2b30c_32c-001}{monoclinic structure}, called ``Mon'' by (Villars, 2018) and ``Type II'' by (Kishida, 1994). \end{itemize}
